    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "MarketUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`MarketUtil` shows an **in-game store** where players can browse and buy products — skins, coins, power-ups. You open a catalog, the player interacts with it, and your script is told what happened."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Showing and hiding the store"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`ShowCatalog(this, catalogId)`", "Opens the store showing the products in catalog `catalogId`."],
                ["`HideCatalog()`", "Closes the store."],
                ["`PurchaseProduct(this, productId, amount)`", "Starts a purchase of a product."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Open the coin shop when the player taps the shop button.",
                "MarketUtil.ShowCatalog(this, \"coins\");"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Hearing what the player did"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "While the catalog is open, the store reports back to your script by calling a method named `MarketEventCall`. Add that method to react to events like a completed purchase."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// The store calls this with an event code and details.",
                "void MarketEventCall(int productEvent, object detail)",
                "{",
                "    // Respond to the store event here (e.g. grant the purchased item).",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "note",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Real money and ownership are handled securely by the platform, not by your script. Your job is to open the catalog and respond to the events it reports through `MarketEventCall`."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`void`", "`ShowCatalog`", "`uniscript, string catalogId`"],
                ["`void`", "`HideCatalog`", "—"],
                ["`void`", "`PurchaseProduct`", "`uniscript, string productId, int amount`"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Pair the store with saved data so purchases stick: when `MarketEventCall` tells you a purchase succeeded, record it with [StorageUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-us/storageutil)."
        }
    ]
}
